%
V:Fl name="Flute"
%slot=lead %role=main_melody %register=upper_mid %dyn=mf %art=staccato+slur
%reason=Solo flute carries the catchy hook motive with staccato attacks and slurred phrase tails. Punchy short cells create earworm recall.
V:Ob name="Oboe"
%slot=countermelody %role=harmonic_answer %register=upper_mid %dyn=p %art=staccato
%reason=Oboe answers the flute in staccato thirds, creating call-and-response catchiness. Drops out at texture drops for contrast.
V:Chip name="Chiptune Pulse"
%slot=color %role=chiptune_mirror %register=high %dyn=pp %art=staccato
%reason=High pulse-wave mirrors the hook staccato. Drops out during breakdown for dramatic re-entry.
V:Hp name="Harp"
%slot=harmony %role=arpeggiated_chords %register=mid %dyn=p %art=arpeggiated
%reason=Harp arpeggios shimmer underneath. Sustains through drops to hold harmonic continuity.
V:Gl name="Glockenspiel"
%slot=color %role=shimmer_accent %register=high %dyn=pp %art=staccato
%reason=Glockenspiel punctuates phrase endings and drop re-entries with bright staccato chimes.
V:Pz name="Violin"
%slot=ostinato %role=pizzicato_pulse %register=mid %dyn=mp %art=staccato
%reason=Pizzicato violins drive the rhythmic engine with tight staccato chord stabs. Core groove element.
V:Ma name="Marimba"
%slot=ostinato %role=warm_pulse %register=mid %dyn=mp %art=staccato
%reason=Marimba interlocks with pizz violins in offset staccato pattern for polyrhythmic groove.
V:Ce name="Cello" clef=bass
%slot=bass %role=walking_bassline %register=low %dyn=mp %art=staccato+legato
%reason=Cello walks with staccato plucks in groovy sections, switches to slurred legato at drops for contrast.
V:Wb name="Woodblock"
%slot=punctuation %role=rhythmic_anchor %register=mid %dyn=p %art=staccato
%reason=Woodblock snaps on beats 1 and 3, drops away for breakdown tension.
V:Sh name="Shaker"
%slot=color %role=rhythmic_texture %register=high %dyn=pp %art=staccato
%reason=Shaker eighth-notes provide constant staccato air. Drops out at breakdowns.
